<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
OK,  i've been wanting to try a group like this for well over a year.  Finally clicked one night in DL on Cazic Thule server.  <BR>grp was as follows:<P>lvl 46 Majjinn mage with Fire pet<BR>lvl 46 Tsalwin mage with Earth<BR>lvl 43-44 Nickk mage with Air (dinged hehe)<P>Tactics were simple.  pet heals were rarely needed.  We roated on the nukes and occationaly all nuked when it was a tough mob.  Between roations on nukes, meding, and pulling we had non stop action similar to enchanter cleric warrior action groups. <P>There was little to no down time (a couple med breaks after several tough mobs in a row) and i'd be willing to bet if we had a mage or two more there would have been no down time at all.  Funny thing is after about 15 min we abandon any attempt to find more for the group.  exp was good and we were recovering from fights at a fast enough rate. <P>the pull:<BR>easiest pulling was with the lvl 8? bolt.  pets could controll aggro really easy with such a low dmg pull.  also the range on the bolt ment that you could keep the pull at max distance and easily be back behind pet lines in time.  I almost never took a hit.  <P>pet tactics:<BR>ha!  leave pets in a pile, naturally keep the Fire shielded and Burned out. Sic em on mob when he's where you want him.  if a pet got down to 20-40 percent of health back him off and let him regen till mob runs.  then send him in for free licks.  usually pets regenerated between fights or because they were not top target and regenerated while fighting. <BR>Pet Observations, an FYI: The lvl 39 air seemed to win the taunt game over the 44 earth and fire pets.  so he had to be pulled out of fight more often.  <P>The next thing i would like to try is a group with 3 air pets.  those stunns would be devistation!.  maybe even gnoll hide wips too, hehe.  or sword of rune's and hunt the summoned hornets in BW.  that would rock. <P>The only thing that could make this group rock harder would have been an enchanter.   Wiz's would be welcom also.  Necros could have filled in for any mage slot where their pets lack there debuffs and dots make up.  With the high regen rates on pets healing class PC's were not needed at all but could save a life if there is an over pull or over burn.  of those classes shm, druid, cleric would have ruled.  a warrior/rouge in such a group would have needed a healer to complement.  but maybe a rouge could get by with proper agro controll. <BR>The knight classes and rng's could have been self suficiant.  <P>Has anyone else out there had similar grouping experiances?  I"d like to hear what combinations you've tried and the pro's and con's to those. <BR>
</FONT>
