Great stories.  for those mages pre 39th lvl.  note your 39th lvl summons pets will get mega bonus on regen rate.  They practically heal all the way between pulls.  This slows down after 39 cause pets get more hit points but even at 44 pets completely heal on a delayed pull.  Save for having a top lvl pet its almost cheaper to resummon if pet is realy low and pulls are relativly fast.   <P>I've recently had some More grp'ing action same as originally posted.  Obvious but not stated bonuses,  Rotate pullers and nukers and you can maintain good mana lvl's with out a chanter.  extra tough mobs are much eaiser to take because chain summoning pets is a lot more casual with multiple pets. <P>I don't know about most mages but I get caught between pets when trying to chain summon solo and it aint pretty.  hehe. <P>-rant- If traditional group would utilize letting pets tank there first 50% of a fight clerics would have a heck of a lot more mana than they normally would having to heal tanks from begining to end of fight.  Pets could blow the roof off group mana efficiantcy.  Funny its so over looked its almost a crime.  I try and teach ppl i group with this but they just ignore me and don't understand -end rant-.<P>Looks like i have a new favorite group besides traditional groups.  Absolutely any class can complement and enjoy a 2 to 3 mage group.  <BR>
