One of the most fun I have ever had was when we had 4 mages, a necro and shammie...talk about damage!<P>We used the necro for crowd control and damage via pet.  We also used darkness ONCE in a while but the mobs where always dead before they could even think about running.<P>We used the shammie to heal(yea right, as if the mobs ever made it to us...mages have phantom armor and necros had lifetaps so heals were VERY few and far between).  Shammie also did slows and damage output via pet.<P>Mages...well, we orginally had 4 53 airs and OMG, the mob never moved...seriously!<P>We soon found out that 4 airs where over kill and went to three and a 54 water...even that was overkill...finally we went to 2 airs and 2 water.  That atleast gave the pets minor damage but they dropped faster.<P>We did the nec/guard in seb and pulled the ENTIRE exit, disco path down to the large bug pull and jail up to the entrance.<P>If any of you out there ever do the nec/guard spawn you will know that is a VERY large amound of mobs before the respawn.  The shammie was chain pulling cause we would kill so fast.<P>Lessons learned:<BR>   All pet groups rule!<P>The only problem we had were the long pulls from the disco path...they were long and sometimes required healing from the necro.<P>-slimer <BR>57.9 mage of inner fire on lanys
