<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I had an interesting experience last night. Well actually the past two nights -- in Dreadlands hunting at the North Wall.<P>Due to my schedule I play late night hours. Well the grouping options at 3am are pretty slim in Dreadlands. <P>So our group last night was:<P>Mage(me)<BR>Shaman<BR>Bard<BR>Wizard<BR>Necro<BR>Cleric<P>Needless to say we were a bit heavy on the caster side. No problem I said! Here was the gameplan... First off the puller is the mage(Shammy SOWs, Cleric Buffs, Necro DMFs). Bard basically sits back and plays mana song. I make an Air pet.<P>I go pull with Malaise and bring it back to the group and between my pet's stun and the cleric's stun the MOB never moves and the Wizzy, Necro, and Shammy nuke it. Bard and pets beat on it(but Bard never stops the mana song) -- MOB drops in the blink of an eye. During the whole time they are fighting and nuking Im sitting getting mana back from Malaise. Luckily there isnt much mana to get back from that cuz I dont sit for long since they drop so fast.<P>But we kept a constant pull and we only had to take a med break if we had a few of those wanderers that joined in. It was pretty impressive that we could drop them baddies so fast and still keep the pulls coming. All I can say is a 40+ Bard Mana song rocks!<P><BR>
</FONT>
