<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
The potential of a multi-mage group inspired me to try something new.  My main is an enchanter, so I get to see a wide variety of groups as I can usually get a group quickly.  Over time I have come to appreciate the damage output of a well played mage.  OMG you guys just rock!<P>Me and 5 friends just started a group. The group will be composed of 4 gnome mages, a gnome enchanter, and a halfling druid (why oh why can't gnomes be druids!).  <P>With disposable pets we don't really need a cleric (one of our members main is a cleric for when we need rezes) and the utility spells of a druid will be invaluable to the group.  The enchanter adds too much to be overlooked.  heck, even with just clarity we would have wanted a chanter.  Since only 4 pets can be on a single mob it seemed overkill to have more than 4 mages.<P>We are getting the group up to 16th level now, and will start adventuring as a group when we get there.  But in leveling up I have seen the potential with just TWO mages, four should be absolutely phenomenal!<P>Anyone have a thought on the best group makeup for a core mage group?  I think the one I have set up is the best for outdoor and indoor play.  I thought about replacing the druid with a shammie since we can all gate, but ports are nice too.  Druids overlap with mages (in that they damage shield), but a shammie slows can be done by the chanter almost as well.<P>Kabober<BR>Gnome Mage<BR>Brell Serilis<P><BR>
</FONT>
