<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Strategies for multi pet groups.  Lets summarize the pro's for pets.  <P>Air: stuns, Tanking via agility (monk style), Medium melee dmg average. (later lvl's not sure)  immune?? <P>Water: Cold dmg nuke, tanking via AC, Medium/Heavy melee dmg average.  (later lvls 39-40, not sure but expect similar to earth) immune poison<P>Earth: Root, Tanking via Hitpoints, Heavy melee dmg average. (later lvls 39-49, Warrior abilities and a lot more knockback during melee) immune??<P>Fire: fire mid lvl fire nukes, all tanking stats are low (like a mage or wiz),  Light/medium Melee, and last but not least a very nice fire dmg shield.  immune fire dmg<P>consider a 3 mage group because I imagine 4 mages of similar lvl would be hard to find. <P>from lvl 4-16 go with mostly fire and either air for some stuns or earth to hold runners and force them onto the dmg shields.  <P>from 20-29 go with Water, Water, Air.  mobs start hitting much harder so you don't want to root unless needed.  when the mob turns to run it free hits for pets if not rooting. <BR>Air, Air, Air could be a hot group too.  variances depend on the mobs being fought. <P>from 29-39 hunt in kedge keep for a 50 to 70 percent exp bonus.  (I've been told there is a 20 for full group bonus, 25 for dungeon, and 25 for underwater zone.)   <P>from 39-49 all kinds of areas are hot.  DL, BW, EJ, Traks Teeth (great camps of mobs around the Seb zone good for 39th lvl groups)<P>Toss in some more killer combination for different zones and lvl's.  I'll compile them all later for a posting on the strategies section.
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
